This paper deals with Boolean networks, which are a type of discrete dynamical systems. The main focus is on the relationship between the number of fixed points and the interaction graph of the network. This topic is relevant to several areas of computer science, including discrete mathematics (cs.DM), social and information networks (cs.SI), neural networks (cs.NE), control systems (cs.SY), and machine learning (cs.LG). Given the emphasis on graph theory and dynamical systems, cs.DM and cs.SI are the most likely categories, followed by cs.NE, cs.SY, and cs.LG.
